<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/9321688-daniel"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1638481129i/9321688._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/9321688-daniel">Daniel</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I agree with all the other answers. Plus, how would she have simply popped him off without drawing attention to herself or getting in a struggle with <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I agree with all the other answers. Plus, how would she have simply popped him off without drawing attention to herself or getting in a struggle with Rudi? If she had sought him out at work or followed him to his flat or something, she would have risked being seen or having a confrontation with him - a much younger and presumably stronger man. In her clever plan, she led him right into her trap and managed events to make herself look like the intended victim! Good ol' Ms. Christie! This is one of my all-time favorite mysteries. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
